<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="44" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[152,1074,272,487]" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">
REMARKS: The new species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Yang &amp; Merz" authorityName="Yang &amp; Merz" authorityYear="2005" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthodes">
<emphasis box="[735,980,273,296]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">Platypalpus xanthodes</emphasis>
Yang &amp; Merz
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[275,370,304,327]" country="China" name="Guangxi" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">Guangxi</collectingRegion>
, but it can be separated from the latter by the left cercus with the acute apical portion short, the right surstylus short and subtriangular with an acute tip, and the left epandrial lamella nearly acute apically. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yang &amp; Merz" authorityYear="2005" box="[733,868,369,392]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthodes">
<emphasis box="[733,868,369,392]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="44">P. xanthodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the left cercus has a long, acute apical portion; the right surstylus is long and somewhat quadrate with a wide and nearly truncate tip; the left epandrial lamella is wide and obtuse apically (
<bibRefCitation author="YANG, D. &amp; MERZ, B." box="[159,379,464,487]" pageId="5" pageNumber="44" pagination="849 - 857" refId="ref2810" refString="YANG, D. &amp; MERZ, B. 2005. Review of the species of Platypalpus Macquart from Guangxi, China (Diptera, Hybotidae, Tachydromiinae). Revue Suisse de Zoologie 112: 849 - 857." type="journal article" year="2005">Yang &amp; Merz, 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
